# Version 0.01 Beta

- Added Two Buttons
    - `mjuiCreateButton` (supports border radius)
        - Supports IDs
    - `mjuiCreateCheckBox` (no support for border radius)

- Added Two Input types
    - `mjuiCreateInput` (supports placeholders)
        - Supports `mjuiGrabInput`
    - `mjuiCreateMultilineInput` (no support for placeholders)
        - Supports `mjuiGrabInput`
        - Added Special function for getting checkbox state, `mjuiCheckButtonGetState`

- Layouts
    - `mjuiCreateLayoutFlex`
        - `MJUI_MJUIEX_VERTICAL`
        - `MJUI_MJUIEX_HORIZONTAL`
            - `RESIZE_XONLY`
            - `RESIZE_YONLY`
            - `RESIZE_XY`

- Added bindings for `mjuiSetWidgetBox`
- Added placeholders for `mjuiCreateInput`, thereby enhancing UX slightly
- Bug fix: `readFromStringBytes` returned a concatenated list of ASCII Char codes instead of the actual string value.

- Update for 25.4
- Added Images and GIF Animations
- Update `mjuiCreateMultiLineInput` to suppot events
- Add new function `mjuiSetInputValue`
- Add new functionality for switching fltk schemes using `useScheme`
- Rename `mjuiSpawnWindow` -> `mjuiCreateWindow`
- Rename `mjuiSetSelectionColor` -> `mjuiSetWidgetSelectionColor`
- Rename `grab_fltk_event` -> `mjuiGrabEvent`
- Implement a new system which auto creates map files (`.map.gen`) based on the header files in  `libc`
- `convertStringToBytes` is now `@always_inline`
- Remove create app script
- Update `README.md`'s example
- Move all old handwritten `.map.gen` files to `maplib/legacy/`
- Add new widget `mjuiScrollContainer` which creates a scrollable container
  - added new functions for the scroll container:
    - `mjuiScrollSetBarBGColor`
    - `mjuiScrollSetBarFGColor`
    - `mjuiScrollScrollBy`

- Added `/scripts`
- Added `build_fltk1.4.sh` for installing and building FLTK1.4 on Linux systems
- Added a better, zero-dependency `create-app.py` which gets a user up and running immediately (OS Support listed in `README.md`)
- Added a `get_started.mojo` template which is used in new apps
- Added `/docs`
- Added `API_REFERENCE.html`
- Added `EXAMPLES.html`